PROJETO-DE-PESQUISA.DESCRICAO-DO-PROJETO:
TIDIA- AE Laboratório Associado LIA (UFSCar). Este laboratório está ligado núcleo TIDIA-AE de Campinas (laboratório e-labora) da Unicamp

The objectives of our research is to offer a set of computational resources that can meet the pedagogical needs of e-learning by:
-Providing computational support based on a set of cognitive strategies to make it easier to build instructional content to be delivered by the educator to the students; 
-Studying teaching and learning methodologies in search of their computational expression to support instructional authoring for DE; 
-Exploring and defining usability criteria of computational resources for DE under the view of educators and students; 
-Investigating pedagogical and HCI patterns, which can increase the production potential of educators in the authoring of instructional content.
The research interests involve also the project, development and evaluation of tools to build educational 3D VEs integrated and synchronized with different media, that can be easily extended and reused, through innovative approaches, such as interactive storytelling. The main features are:
-Faster development of 3D VEs for educational games and/or training courses; 
-More efficient interaction between 3D learning VEs developpers, which typically involves different professionals, with different capabilities, for the specification and implementation of educational games or training courses (for instance, computer graphics professionals, computer programmers and K12 teachers); 
-Extensibility and faster reconfiguration of existing VEs by altering the story corresponding to a VE, instead of altering its supporting system, as done by most of current systems.
